# PHASE 7C.4 — Homepage Why Choose Us Component

## Structured Component Migration

**Project:** The Lylods Group Laravel Platform  
**Phase:** 7C.4  
**Status:** Planned  
**Priority:** High  
**Architecture:** Structured Enterprise CMS, not a page builder

---

# Objective

Extract the homepage **Why Choose Us / Why Clients Choose Us** section into a reusable Blade component while preserving the current public design exactly.

This is a refactor only.

No visual redesign.  
No CMS restructuring.  
No page-builder behaviour.  
No new database work.

---

# Current Completed Slices

Already completed:

- Hero component
- Statistics component
- Services component

This slice continues the same pattern.

---

# Core Rule

The homepage remains developer-composed.

The CMS may manage content.

The CMS must not manage page structure.

Do not introduce:

- page sections table
- drag-and-drop ordering
- arbitrary page composition
- generic component resolver
- page-builder canvas
- JSON layout builder
- Elementor-style behaviour

---

# Scope

Only work on the homepage Why Choose Us section.

Do not touch:

- About page
- Services page
- Admin dashboard
- Investor dashboard
- Auth pages
- Routes
- Controllers
- Models
- Migrations
- SEO system
- Sitemap
- Structured data
- Media library logic

---

# Target Component

Create:

```text
resources/views/components/sections/why-choose-us.blade.php
```

If the feature cards repeat heavily, optionally create:

```text
resources/views/components/cards/feature-card.blade.php
```

Only create the card component if it reduces duplication without changing the rendered output.

---

# Expected Usage

Homepage should call the section directly:

```blade
<x-sections.why-choose-us
    :eyebrow="$eyebrow ?? null"
    :heading="$heading ?? null"
    :description="$description ?? null"
    :items="$items ?? []"
/>
```

If the current section is hardcoded, pass the same static data as an array from the homepage Blade.

Do not connect it to CMS data unless it is already connected today.

---

# Component Responsibilities

The component may render:

- section wrapper
- eyebrow
- heading
- description
- feature grid
- feature cards
- icons
- links if already present
- responsive layout
- fallback state

The component must not:

- query the database
- decide page order
- load unrelated content
- modify data
- create dynamic section behaviour

---

# Data Supported

Each item should support:

```text
icon
title
description
link label
link URL
```

Only include link fields if links already exist in the current section.

---

# Visual Preservation

The output must remain visually identical.

Preserve:

- Tailwind classes
- spacing
- typography
- colours
- grid structure
- card layout
- icon treatment
- hover behaviour
- responsive behaviour
- section background
- CTA placement if present

Do not improve the design in this slice.

---

# Fallback Behaviour

If there are no items:

- do not crash
- hide the grid or section gracefully
- avoid empty broken markup

If heading or description is missing:

- omit only that element
- keep layout stable

---

# Accessibility Requirements

Maintain:

- heading hierarchy
- semantic section structure
- accessible links
- icon treatment
- keyboard focus states
- readable text contrast

Decorative icons should not create screen-reader noise.

---

# Performance Requirements

Do not introduce:

- new database queries
- N+1 queries
- repeated heavy parsing
- additional services

This should be a Blade extraction only.

---

# Files Expected to Change

Expected new file:

```text
resources/views/components/sections/why-choose-us.blade.php
```

Optional new file:

